      <summary><span>What is agentic commerce for Shopify?</span><span class="faq-arrow">▼</span></summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Agentic commerce refers to AI agents (like those in ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google Gemini, and emerging shopping assistants) discovering, comparing, and potentially purchasing products on behalf of users. For Shopify stores to appear in these experiences, they need machine-readable structured data, clear product specifications, and well-structured content that AI can parse and summarise.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary><span>How do I make my Shopify store appear in Google AI Overviews?</span><span class="faq-arrow">▼</span></summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>The key factors are: strong structured data (Product, FAQPage, HowTo schema), clear factual content that answers specific questions, fast page speed (Core Web Vitals), and authority signals (backlinks, brand mentions). FAQ schema is particularly effective — Google often pulls FAQ answers directly into AI Overviews.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary><span>Does Shopify add structured data automatically?</span><span class="faq-arrow">▼</span></summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Shopify themes add basic Product schema for product pages. However, most themes do not automatically add FAQPage, HowTo, Review, or BreadcrumbList schema. These require either theme customisation, a schema app, or custom code. Without them, your store is invisible to a significant portion of AI search queries.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary><span>What is GEO and how is it different from SEO?</span><span class="faq-arrow">▼</span></summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>GEO (Generative Engine Optimisation) refers to optimising content to be cited and referenced by AI-powered answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, and Google's AI Overviews. Unlike traditional SEO which focuses on ranking positions, GEO focuses on making your content the authoritative answer that AI systems cite. Key tactics include structured data, direct factual statements, and content that answers specific questions concisely.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary><span>Is chat support like Tidio important for AI readiness?</span><span class="faq-arrow">▼</span></summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Live chat and chatbot tools like Tidio improve AI readiness indirectly by capturing intent data from customers, providing FAQ content that can be structured, and improving engagement metrics that signal content quality to AI systems. For direct AI readiness, the bigger priorities are structured data and content quality.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
